{"content_excerpt":"# apps/rt — `mustard-rt`\n\nSubproject guard for the Mustard runtime crate. Auto-loaded when working under `apps/rt/`.\n\n## What this is\n\nThe `mustard-rt` crate — the single enforcement + automation binary. It has three\nfaces:\n\n- **Hooks** (`src/hooks/`) — one module per concern (`bash_guard`, `budget`,\n  `close_gate`, `model_routing`, `tracker`, …). `settings.json` wires one\n  `mustard-rt on <event>` entry per lifecycle event; `dispatch.rs` runs every\n  module registered for that event.\n- **Run subcommands** (`src/run/`) — `mustard-rt run <name>`: `sync-detect`,\n  `sync-registry`, `scan-orchestrate`, `scan-finalize`, `verify-pipeline`,\n  `security-scan`, and more. These replaced the old JS `scripts/` payload.\n- **MCP** (`src/mcp/`) — the Rust MCP server face.\n\n## Build & test\n\n```bash\ncargo build -p mustard-rt\ncargo test  -p mustard-rt\ncargo run   -p mustard-rt -- run sync-detect      # discover subprojects (JSON)\ncargo run   -p mustard-rt -- run scan-orchestrate # /scan pre-dispatch\n```\n\n## Guards\n\n- **Fail open.** Hook dispatch must never abort user work — per-step errors are\n  reported inside the JSON result; the process exits `0`.\n- **Run subcommands emit byte-stable JSON.** The pipeline parses stdout; keep\n  field order and the two-space pretty layout when porting/altering output.\n- Assets a binary must read but does not distribute (e.g. the scan agent-prompt\n  template) are embedded via `include_str!`, with an on-disk copy as optional\n  override — do not reintroduce hard file dependencies.\n- Code, comments and doc-comments in EN; surgical edits only.\n- `unsafe` is forbidden (`#![forbid(unsafe_code)]`); `unwrap_used` is `deny` in non-test code.\n- Add enforcement modules by appending to `Registry::new()` — never modify the dispatcher.\n- `rusqlite` pinned to `0.31` — matches dashboard `src-tauri` to share `libsqlite3-sys`.\n- Subprocess calls: `cmd /C` on Windows, `sh -c` on POSIX.\n- Telemetry: always `let _ = store.append(...)` — never load-bearing.\n\n## Stack\n\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Language | Rust (edition 2024, rust-version 1.85) |\n| Dependencies | `mustard-core`, `serde_json`, `clap`, `tiny_http`, `rusqlite` (bundled 0.31), `rmcp`, `tokio` (current_thread, mcp only) |\n| Binary faces | `on <event>`, `check <id>`, `run <subcommand>`, `mcp` |\n\n## Statusline themes\n\n`mustard-rt run statusline` reads `MUSTARD_STATUSLINE_THEME` (defaults to `catppuccin`). Accepted values: `default`, `minimal`, `tokyo-night`, `catppuccin`, `pastel-powerline`, `gruvbox-rainbow`. Powerline themes require a Nerd Font; users without one should set `MUSTARD_STATUSLINE_THEME=default`. Preview all themes with `mustard-rt run statusline --preview`.\n\n## Commands\n\n```bash\ncargo build -p mustard-rt\ncargo test  -p mustard-rt\ncargo run   -p mustard-rt -- run sync-detect\ncargo run   -p mustard-rt -- run scan-orchestrate\ncargo run   -p mustard-rt -- run sync-registry\ncargo run   -p mustard-rt -- run qa-run --spec <name>\ncargo run   -p mustard-rt -- mcp\n```\n\n## Recommended Skills\n\n- `.claude/skills/rt-hook-module-pattern/` — adding/modifying enforcement modules\n- `.claude/skills/rt-run-subcommand-pattern/` — adding/porting run-face subcommands\n- `.claude/skills/rt-fail-open-dispatch-pattern/` — dispatcher, protocol, verdict folding\n\n## Scan References\n\nGenerated by `/mustard:scan` on 2026-05-19.\n\n| File | Contents |\n|---|---|\n| `.claude/commands/stack.md` | Language, dependencies, build commands |\n| `.claude/commands/modules.md` | All modules, run subcommands, MCP tools |\n| `.claude/commands/patterns.md` | 10 recurring implementation patterns |\n| `.claude/commands/guards.md` | DO/DON'T rules for safe extension |\n| `.claude/commands/recipes.md` | Skeletons for the 3 most common tasks |\n| `.claude/skills/rt-hook-module-pattern/` | How to add an enforcement module |\n| `.claude/skills/rt-run-subcommand-pattern/` | How to add a run-face subcommand |\n| `.claude/skills/rt-fail-open-dispatch-pattern/` | Dispatcher + protocol + fail-open |\n\n## Scan subsystem (project-profiler Wave 2)\n\nThere is **no per-language scanner** under `sr... [truncated, 1866 bytes more]","file_path":"C:\\Atiz\\mustard\\apps\\rt\\CLAUDE.md","tool":"Read","tool_use_id":"toolu_018CdZMecYgvasFoEGE3WvXv"}